119558/image_1053119558.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1053119558/image_1053119558.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1053119558/image_1053119558.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1053119558/image_1053119558.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1053119558/image_1053119558.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1053119558/image_1053119558.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">ablokhin</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Introduction</h2> <p>It's been more than a year since I covered trucking company Old Dominion Freight Line (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ODFL\" title=\"Old Dominion Freight Line, Inc.\">ODFL</a></span>). Since writing on them, the stock has faced headwinds; I'll touch on that later in this article.</p> <p>However, the company's financials have</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1053119558/image_1053119558.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4745052-old-dominion-freight-line-dividend-grower-benefit-from-lower-interest-rates", "pub_date": "2024-12-20 16:00:00", "source": "seekalpha_articles", "kind": 1, "language": "en"}, {"id": "4745556", "title": "The Top Investment Trends For Ultra-High Net Worth Investors In 2025", "description": "<p></p> <p>Syed Naqvi, Managing Principal at TD Wealth Family Office, and Brad Simpson, Chief Wealth Strategist, TD Wealth Investment Office, speak with MoneyTalk\u2019s Greg Bonnell about the evolving investment landscape in 2025 and how ultra-high net worth families are positioning themselves.</p> <h2>Transcript </h2> <p><strong>Greg Bonnell:</strong> Equity markets have had a stellar run, spending much of 2024 in record territory. But what can we expect for 2025, especially amid ongoing geopolitical conflicts, potential trade tariffs, and economic uncertainty? Here to discuss the big themes of this year and next is Syed Naqvi, Managing Principal of TD Wealth Family Office, and Brad Simpson, Chief Wealth Strategist at TD Wealth Investment Office.</p> <p>Great to have you guys here for this discussion. Syed, I'm going to start with you about some of the investing trends you saw for the ultra-high-net-worth client this year.</p> <p><strong>Syed Naqvi:</strong> Thanks, Greg, for having me. So for 2024, we would break down the trends in three different categories. From an investment management perspective, maintaining purchasing power remained the paramount concern for family offices and ultra-high-net-worth clients. We saw some really good data for inflation, where we saw inflation numbers come down. But in real terms, asset prices remained quite elevated, and that meant that you were solving for higher hurdle rates when it came to your portfolios. So in that kind of an environment, we saw risk assets do really, really well. Equities had a record year. And anything tied to real assets-- such as commodities, infrastructure, private equity-- they did really, really well.</p> <p>Secondly, from a thematic perspective, AI and technology-related themes continue to thrive. We saw spectacular performance from the Mag 7 stocks, NASDAQ and S&amp;P 500 as a whole. But we thought that there was a lot of breadth to this theme across different asset classes. So even if we look at private real</p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4745556-top-investment-trends-for-ultra-high-net-worth-investors-2025", "pub_date": "2024-12-20 15:50:00", "source": "seekalpha_articles", "kind": 1, "language": "en"}, {"id": "4745540", "title": "Teladoc: Attractive Valuation, But The Narrative Stalls", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Stethoscope checking health of Credit card\" data-id=\"2143914595\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"987px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2143914595/image_2143914595.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">J Studios</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>I see Teladoc Health, Inc. (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TDOC\" title=\"Teladoc Health, Inc.\">TDOC</a></span>) as a prime example of a stock with attractive valuation ratios, yet most investors remain unconvinced